(282, 'news', 'news_content', 2, '\n                        \n                        \n                        \n                        \n                        <ul class=\"move-ul \"><li style=\"font-size: 0;\"><div class=\"imageContainer ne\" style=\"width:100%;display: inline-block; padding:10px; font-size:14px;\"><p></p><p></p><div class=\"det-pic test1 flex-sb\">\n                <img src=\"../images/01.jpg\" alt=\"\">\n                <img src=\"../images/02.jpg\" alt=\"\">\n            </div>\n<p>When it comes to Type C, you have to say the development of USB. USB Chinese is called Universal Serial Bus Interface. It is divided into Type A (computer) and \n                Type B (printer) to meet the needs of different devices. In addition to the standard form, there are Micro and The Mini type interface is used for small-sized \n                devices such as mobile phones and tablets. The development of USB is from 1.0-2.0, 3.0-the latest 3.1 interface, but the types are too complicated. For example, \n                the Type A interfaces of USB2.0 and USB 3.0 can be used interchangeably, while the Micro and Mini interfaces cannot.</p>\n            <div class=\"hdmi-cont test1\">\n                <img src=\"../images/03.jpg\" alt=\"\">\n                <p>After the development of the USB 3.1 standard, with the upgrade of consumer demand, how to make a data line meet the needs of most devices has become the fundamental \n                    of many users. Under such circumstances, USB-IF announced the introduction of Type C interface. . This kind of interface avoids the embarrassment that the nine \n                    people of the traditional USB interface are plugged in for the first time. The advantage is that it is small in size, can carry up to 10Gbps data transmission speed, \n                    can withstand 100W power transmission, and can also be used for video transmission.</p>\n                <img src=\"../images/04.jpg\" alt=\"\">\n                <p>Type C belongs to the interface specification. Lightning 3 belongs to the physical layer and uses the Type C interface. It belongs to the specification standard and \n                    does not conflict with Type C. If it is to be compared, it should be compared with the USB 3.1/3.2 interface because lightning is led and developed by Intel. \n                    In the process, the bandwidth can reach 40Gbps, which is up to 4 times compared with the 10Gbps of USB 3.1. Previously, due to interface limitations and other \n                    reasons, it was not widely used in the market. However, starting from Lightning 3, Intel has adopted the interface specification based on the Type C physical layer, \n                    and is fully capable of implementing most of the functions of USB Type C, and the transmission rate is higher. The achievable content is richer.</p>\n                <p>Therefore, the interface specification adopted by Thunderbolt 3 is Type C, so USB 3.1 is supported at the same time; however, the Type C interface device supporting \n                    USB 3.1 does not necessarily support the lightning specification interface. At present, all lightning-supported lightning bolts are located next to the interface \n                    that supports Thunderbolt 3. In general, Thunderbolt 3 is trustworthy in terms of performance. In terms of development trend, Thunder Power 3 will appear more and \n                    more in our daily sight as the market share increases.</p>\n            </div><p></p><p></p><p></p></div><div class=\"mask\" style=\"display: none;\"><a class=\"pull-right remove\" href=\"javascript:void(0);\"><i class=\"fa fa-trash-o\"></i></a><a class=\"pull-right copy\" href=\"javascript:void(0);\"><i class=\"fa fa-clipboard\"></i></a><a class=\"pull-right edit\" data-attr=\"text-block\" href=\"javascript:void(0);\"><i class=\"fa fa-pencil-square-o\"></i></a></div></li></ul>                                                                                                    '),
